:: intro {"position":"800,300","size":"100,100"}
Welcome to SkyCab! You’re the software dev behind Muncie's first autonomous air taxi. Your code will decide if passengers get smooth skies or a less than favorable fate.

[[start]]


:: jobMarket {"position":"700,2300","size":"100,100"}
You decide to let the fire burn

While, initially, the air taxes are performing well, more and more bad press about their lack of reliability becomes widespread.

The company aims for an effective re-brand, and an associated rewrite of parts of the codebase.

You start to overhear information from the team responsible for handling large scale data collection. Apparently, security is poorly configured here. It gets to a point that you are concerned about the possibility for a data breach if this isn’t handled.

[[Let the fire burn->leakFear]]
[[Speak with a higher up->notifySomeone]] 


