Unfortunately, your fears were realized. Tons of user data has been leaked. With this new 
PR issue, the company is struggling, and looking to cut heads.

Unfortunately, you’ve now been laid-off.

The company, being crippled under lawsuits, chooses to sell one of its final assets: its remaining user data.

[[Back to start->start]]


:: maintenanceHub {"position":"700,1900","size":"100,100"}
The passenger loses their apointment, but the risk is completely mitigated

[[Continue->scenario5]]


:: notifySomeone {"position":"900,2300","size":"100,100"}
You talk with your manager, doing your best to fully explain the issue.

While they don’t dismiss the problem, they reiterate how tight of a deadline this project is on. Even with the bugs, it’s forced to continue.

Knowing some of the implications of this, you feel frustrated with the lack of proper attention to the issue. You start to feel concerned about the state of these vehicles.

[[Tell friends/family that these cars have problems, losing potential customers->fired]]
[[Continue->dangerousFear]]


:: park {"position":"700,1100","size":"100,100"}
Land in the park. More lives are at risk, but it’s an open space and easier for the system to land safely.

[[Continue->scenario3]] 


:: pushback {"position":"900,700","size":"100,100"}
Delaying the trial ensures the system is safe, tested, and reliable, aligning with the ethical responsibility of reducing harm.

[[Continue->scenario2]]


:: scenario2 {"position":"800,900","size":"100,100"}
Your air taxi loses navigation control mid-flight and must land immediately. There are only two possible emergency landing zones left:

[[A crowded public park with 30 people->park]]
[[A rooftop bar helipad where 2 maintenance workers are present.->bar]]


:: scenario3 {"position":"800,1300","size":"100,100"}
While programming, you realize the AI model sometimes behaves unpredictably in bad weather conditions, but the team lead says, “We'll deal with that post-launch.”

[[Leave the bug for later—no one’s likely to test it when the weather is bad anyway->badWeather]]
[[Flag it as a critical safety risk and delay release until it's resolved->flagRisk]]


:: scenario4 {"position":"800,1700","size":"100,100"}
Your air taxi detects a mechanical failure during flight. It can still complete the trip—but the system estimates a 10% chance of catastrophic failure before landing.

[[Divert immediately even though the passenger will miss a doctor’s apointment.->maintenanceHub]]
[[Continue the flight to their destination, risking a fatal mid-air failure.->doctorAppointment]]


:: scenario5 {"position":"800,2100","size":"100,100"}
You start to notice tons of potential bugs. Race conditions in the model, design flaws, and certain ethical dilemmas are entirely overlooked.

The entire state of the model is at an impasse, as it’s plagued with issues.

You have to talk with your manager

[[The job market is really tough right now...->jobMarket]]
[[Someone needs to know about this->notifySomeone]]


:: setback {"position":"700,700","size":"100,100"}
Fulfilling the deadline despite known bugs prioritizes managerial approval and deadlines over user safety, which is ethically irresponsible.

[[Continue->scenario2]]


:: start {"position":"800,500","size":"100,100"}
You begin programming the taxi and your first trial run is comming up, but you know that there’s still bugs you need to fix and dont feel ready yet.

What should you do:
[[Fulfill the deadline, your superiors will be unhappy if you have another setback.->setback]]
[[Push back the deadline, and wait until you know you have everything in order for a successful trial run.->pushback]]

